productName: Spring Valley Melatonin Tablets Dietary Supplement, 5 mg, 120 Count
text: I used to have trouble staying asleep once I fell asleep, so I started taking melatonin. I was taking two three milligram tablets but that wasn't doing it. I decided to try the five milligram tablets, and that did the trick. An hour before bedtime, I take two tablets with water, and once I fall asleep, I stay asleep for eight hours straight. I don't wake up until it is time to wake up, and that has been a delight for me. It is wonderful to wake up feeling refreshed and wide awake. Melatonin has a reputation for causing odd dreams, and I have experienced that with other brands, but this brand makes me sleep so well that I don't generally recall my dreams, let alone if they were odd. The only thing that would make these better, would be if I slept for nine or ten hours! That is only because I spent years and years with insomnia to varying degrees. Eight hours does it for me, and I don't really need more than that. I wish I could sleep well, but without this I can't. I will buy this for the rest of my life. It really does help me sleep, and I stay sleeping. My daughter was in the military and frequently deployed overseas. She told me that the military told them to take ten milligrams of melatonin if they had trouble sleeping until they acclimated to the time changes. It worked well for her on the occasions she needed it, and it works for me all the time.

productName: Swanson Dietary Supplements Triple Strength Melatonin 10 mg Capsule 60ct
text:
I have mixed feelings about Swanson's Triple Strength Melatonin. It works about 50% of the time for me. I've always been an inconsistent sleeper, especially when I drink too much caffeine during the day. On those days, I take one Triple Strength Melatonin with water about an hour before bed. Sometimes it works great, sometimes it kind of works and sometimes it doesn't work at all.

When it works great, I have no problem falling asleep and staying asleep - it's an awesome restful night of sleep.

When it kind of works, I still have a hard time falling asleep but I can sleep the whole night once I'm asleep OR I can fall asleep but I'm wide awake after about 4 hours of sleep and I have an awful time falling back asleep. I'm usually awake for 2-3 hours before I fall back asleep.

And when it doesn't work at all, it's like I never took one. I have a really hard time falling asleep and when I finally do, it's a very light sleep with a lot of tossing and turning.

The good thing is when I do wake up in the morning, I don't experience a sleep "hangover". I don't know if it's possible to get "duds" in a batch but the 50/50 odds are strange.

text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I've never tried sleeping aids, but thought I would give these a try since I've heard so much about melatonin and I tend to have trouble falling asleep at night. They did help me fall asleep more quickly, which was very nice, but they also made me very drowsy during the day and I kept waking up with headaches. The worst part, though, was that I started having vivid dreams that often shifted into nightmares that would wake me up in the middle of the night. I looked it up and this can be a side effect of melatonin because it keeps you in the stage of sleep that often features intense dreams. I think this could be a good product for other people, but you have to be careful with how your body will handle it. The side effects just weren't worth it for me.

text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] “Springing forward” is always tough for me, as I am one of those “early to bed, early to rise.”  It can be quite difficult cognitively to prepare for bed and get in bed when it is still light outside, and my body is clearly not in sync with the time.  I took this supplement for a few days after the time change, and it helped me to feel tired and sleepy at my usual wind-down and bedtimes, despite differences in external light.  I took it about 40 minutes before my desired bedtime, and it didn't interfere with what I was doing, just helped me feel ready for bed.  Of worthy note is that there are no clear directions on the bottle to dissolve the tablet on your tongue (vs. swallowing, which is more traditional for a pill).
title: Helpful supplement, especially with time change.

productName: Natrol Melatonin 10 mg Fast-Dissolve Strawberry30.0ea
text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I want to start off by stating I've never used Melatonin products so I cannot compare it to other brands. I can provide a comparison to Nyquil ( which is totally a different type of medicine). I thought that the effects of Melatonin were going to be similar to Nyquil so I wanted to make sure I was prepared to intake. With NyQuil I gave myself plenty of time to sleep and knew that I would have a hard time waking up. Also with NyQuil it would Knock me out pretty quickly and hard, if I fought it then I would get confused because I would be too tired. With Natrol Melatonin I feel like it really helps me calm down from a long day and aids me to sleep. It doesn't just knock me out instantly. I can wake up and be coherent and function. It doesn't make me feel frowny either. When I had caffeine late in the day, I know I can use this to help me calm down and get some rest. Again, I'm just comparing the effects of both just to shed some light for people that never taken melatonin. I've never woken up feeling tired or feeling weird after taking Natrol Melatonin. I believe it great for sleep aid.
title: Peaceful nights

text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I received a bottle of Natrol Melatonin 10 mg fast dissolving strawberry flavor in the mail this past week. Ever since covid started, I've had such a horrible sleeping pattern. I use to be able to sleep 8 hour's a night, but I'm lucky if I get 4 hour's now. I started taking 2 tablet's before bed to help get back on a sleeping pattern. Now I only take 1 tablet 30 minutes before bed and if I wake up in the middle of the night I only take 5mg. I sleep all night long now without every waking up, and when I wake up in the mornings I wake up so refreshed and ready to start my day. My teenager also takes 1 tablet before bed and he wakes up every morning ready for school and then goes to work feeling amazing from having a great night of sleep! I highly recommend trying these if you need to get back on a good sleeping pattern.

text:
I have been using Natrol Melatonin 5mg fast dissolve for a couple of years. They tasted great and work well. I occasionally take 2 tablets, so I figured I'd just get the 10mg this time. Huge mistake! Yes, they work but the ingredients are different and they taste HORRIBLE!!! (And they take longer to dissolve!) The primary sweetener in the 10 mg is dextrose and it contains artificial strawberry flavor as well as menthol (The primary sweetener in the 5mg is xylitol and it contains natural flavors) 
I wish I had just gotten 2 bottles of 5mg instead of the 10mg because I wasted my money on the NASTY 10mg!!!

productName: Spring Valley Liquid Melatonin Dietary Supplement, 10 mg, 2 fl oz
text:
For someone with chronic insomnia such as myself, this stuff is a godsend.
The taste is much better than the majority of the alternatives... especially when they're generally a weaker concentration.
I ordered four since my store's been out of stock recently, but they had all crystalized -- big ol flakes. Since they specifically added a new storage warning about the temperature (and a little chemistry knowledge), I figured a little heat would do the trick. 

Popped it in the microwave for 10 seconds, and after a little bit the crystals all dissolved back into solution. You don't want to get it too hot though, and leave the cap loose or you'll be heating a sealed container. Don't do that. Exercise caution as usual... Or don't. It's the inside of *your* microwave you'll have to clean, not mine.

Either way, it's a minor flaw with an easy fix, and the stuff works like a charm. Sweet dreams, y'all.
title: Insomniacs' Dream

text: I use these for myself because they are one of the only 1mg of melatonin I can find. People need to dive into melatonin dosage research more. I'm an adult and overweight if you want to consider weight factor into dosage and when I do take this, I take half a tablet (0.5mg). I never wake up groggy after taking half a tablet and it gives me enough push to fall asleep. On 3mg  I tend to have nightmares and wake up groggy. I imagine it's the same for many adults and children but it's not widely known that melatonin should be taken in extremely small dosages because many tablets are 5mg-10mg. You and your child should be taking the smallest dose possible to help you fall asleep, not make you fall asleep. As far as this brand, I love it. I like the ingredients and although I think their dosage recommendations are too high, they're a lot better than the 10mg gummies people eat like snacks.

I thought that the effects of Melatonin were going to be similar to Nyquil so I wanted to make sure I was prepared to intake. With NyQuil I gave myself plenty of time to sleep and knew that I would have a hard time waking up. Also with NyQuil it would Knock me out pretty quickly and hard, if I fought it then I would get confused because I would be too tired. With Natrol Melatonin I feel like it really helps me calm down from a long day and aids me to sleep. It doesn't just knock me out instantly. I can wake up and be coherent and function. It doesn't make me feel frowny either. When I had caffeine late in the day, I know I can use this to help me calm down and get some rest. Again, I'm just comparing the effects of both just to shed some light for people that never taken melatonin. I've never woken up feeling tired or feeling weird after taking Natrol Melatonin. I believe it great for sleep aid.
